The Problem
The MRR workflow has two different permission strategies coexisting:

permission_check_node (lines 247-421) uses AuthController.check_agent_access for creator/pl_approver — the correct, DB-driven approach
But for approver/erp_approver/issuer, it falls back to hardcoded approvers.py lists
Then the nodes re-check the same hardcoded lists again (redundant)
Meanwhile, pl_pm_agent_node does it the right way — querying the database at runtime for project-specific assignments. This is the pattern used by RMS and HRMS workflows throughout the codebase.

The fix would be to move the approver/erp_approver/issuer checks to use AuthController.check_agent_access (or a similar DB-driven approach) instead of approvers.py, aligning MRR with the rest of the codebase.
